{
  "_comment": [
    "All hosting sites (dinify-prod, dinify-dev, dinify-stage, dinify-uat) live",
    "under the 'dinify-dev' Firebase project. The project name is misleading — it",
    "is not limited to development use. Do NOT rename projects or targets without",
    "updating the deploy-prod.yml workflow and coordinating with the team.",
    "",
    "The 'targets' block maps the deploy target name 'dinify-prod' to the Firebase",
    "hosting site 'dinify-prod'. 'dinify-prod' is now the live, CI-deployed target:",
    "it is referenced by the deploy-prod.yml GitHub Actions workflow, which deploys",
    "on every merge to main. The 'dinify-dev', 'dinify-stage', and 'dinify-uat'",
    "sites/targets are legacy and pending removal in a later cleanup PR (kept for",
    "now until the prod deploy is verified live). The dinify-dev and dinify-stage",
    "sites in firebase.json do not have explicit target mappings here — they are",
    "deployed directly by site name (e.g. firebase deploy --only hosting:dinify-dev)."
  ],
  "projects": {
    "default": "dinify-dev",
    "prod": "dinify-dev",
    "uat": "dinify-dev"
  },
  "targets": {
    "dinify-dev": {
      "hosting": {
        "dinify-prod": [
          "dinify-prod"
        ],
        "dinify-uat": [
          "dinify-uat"
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}
